text.tspan: Private green energy generation is on the rise.
Photovoltaic (PV) can provide an accessible way to
achieve energy independence by making energy
generation and consumption possible at home. But
convenient electricity at night and on cloudy days
requires combining self-supply with on-site energy
storage capacity.
Hybrid inverters cover both requirements. They connect
multiple PV panels and convert the generated direct
current (DC) to alternating current (AC) that home
appliances use. And they can also supply DC current
directly to Energy Storage Systems, e.g. batteries.
Our semiconductors make all this possible. See where
and how.
